articles.title: Iran’s Incompetent Response to Coronavirus Threatens the Middle East and the World
articles.description: Iran has responded to the coronavirus in a characteristically counterproductive fashion.

articles.author: Zachary Evans, Zachary Evans
articles.title: Iran to Sentence Citizens Who “Spreads Rumors” about Coronavirus to Flogging, Three Years in Prison
articles.description: An Iranian parliament spokesman on Wednesday announced the decision, in response to a growing number of cases of the contagious respiratory disease in Iran.

articles.author: Mairead McArdle
articles.title: Schumer Requests $8.5 Billion in Coronavirus Funds, Accuses Trump Admin. of ‘Dangerous Incompetence’
articles.description: Senator Chuck Schumer requested $8.5 billion in emergency funding to combat the coronavirus, more than three times the amount the White House has requested.

articles.author: Zachary Evans, Zachary Evans
articles.title: Beijing’s Handling of Coronavirus Has Undermined Chinese Public’s Trust in State Media
articles.description: China has changed its diagnostic criteria for the coronavirus multiple times, leading to confusion over the number of confirmed cases in the country.

articles.author: Tobias Hoonhout, Tobias Hoonhout
articles.title: U.S. Soldier Infected with Coronavirus in South Korea, Officials Say
articles.description: Officials said that the soldier had visited the American military base in the Korean city of Daegu — the epicenter of the outbreak in South Korea.
